    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">FAQ</div>
        <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
          Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details open class="group border border-border">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">
              Who are the largest conveyor manufacturers?
              <span class="ml-4 text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
              <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">Major conveyor manufacturers include Hytrol, Dorner, Interroll, mk North America, Bastian Solutions (now a Toyota Advanced Logistics company), Dematic, Honeywell Intelligrated, and Siemens Logistics. In food and packaging specifically, Key Technology, Heat and Control, Intralox (a Laitram company), Wire Belt Company, and Nercon are well-known. The largest players vary by conveyor type and industry , a company that dominates warehouse sortation may not build sanitary food conveyors.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-border">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">
              How do I choose a conveyor manufacturer?
              <span class="ml-4 text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
              <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">Start by defining your application requirements: product type, weight, speed, environment (washdown, cleanroom, outdoor), and any regulatory standards (FDA, USDA, ATEX). Then evaluate manufacturers based on relevant experience in your industry, geographic proximity for service and installation, lead time, warranty terms, parts availability, and controls integration capability. Request references from similar installations and ask for a factory visit or demo if possible.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-border">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">
              What is the difference between a conveyor manufacturer and an integrator?
              <span class="ml-4 text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
              <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">A conveyor manufacturer designs and builds conveyor equipment , they fabricate frames, assemble drives, and ship the physical hardware. An integrator designs the overall material handling system, selects equipment from one or more manufacturers, handles controls and software, manages installation, and commissions the complete system. Some companies do both; others specialize in one role. For simple single-conveyor purchases, buying direct from a manufacturer is common. For complex multi-zone systems, an integrator adds value through system design and project management.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-border">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">
              Do conveyor manufacturers sell direct or through distributors?
              <span class="ml-4 text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
              <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">It varies by company. Some manufacturers like Dorner and mk North America sell both direct and through distributor networks. Others like Hytrol sell primarily through a network of integration partners. Large system manufacturers like Dematic and Honeywell Intelligrated typically sell direct through their own sales engineering teams. For packaging-specific conveyors, many manufacturers sell direct because the applications require custom engineering. Always check the manufacturer's website for their preferred sales channel in your region.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-border">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">
              Can I buy conveyor parts from any manufacturer?
              <span class="ml-4 text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
              <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">Many conveyor components , rollers, bearings, motors, VFDs, belting, and chain , are available from third-party suppliers and are not proprietary to the conveyor manufacturer. However, some manufacturers use proprietary frame profiles, belt lacing systems, or controller software that requires OEM parts. Before purchasing a conveyor, ask the manufacturer what percentage of wear parts are standard catalog items versus proprietary components. This affects long-term maintenance costs and parts availability.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
